South African police clashed with about 1 200 supporters of the opposition Economic Freedom Fighters party on Friday who were protesting against alleged racism at a Cape Town school. The protesters gathered outside the Brackenfell High School two hours earlier than their protest permit allowed and the police confronted them with stun grenades, tear gas and water cannons after they threw stones at the school buildings. Subscribe for full access to all our share and unit trust data tools, our award-winning articles, and support quality journalism in the process. You will be redirected to a checkout page.
